data.enText: to leave your own country to go and live permanently in another country

data.chText: 犹太人从东欧往其他地区的大批移居
data.enText: the mass emigration of Jews from Eastern Europe

simple_means.memory_skill: e 出，外 + migr 迁移 + ate 表动词 → 移居国外

tr: leave one's country of residence for a new one
example: Many people had to emigrate during the Nazi period

value.def: If you emigrate, you leave your own country to live in another country.

example.ex: ...the huge emigration of workers to the West.
example.tran: 工人向西方国家的大规模移民
